	     Durban – Police are searching for a missing 10-year-old boy after the body of his friend – who was last seen with him – was found in a bush in Montclair, Durban. Luyanda Msomi and his friend Njabulo Mankanyi, who are both Grade 3 pupils at Clairwood Boys Primary School, were last seen boarding a bus to go home last Tuesday. ALSO READ: Boy, 11, found floating in river with multiple stab wounds Msomi's bruised body was found by police in a dense bush in Montclair on Saturday. However, Mankanyi has not yet been found. Colonel Thembeka Mbhele said on Monday that police arrested two women "after an intensive investigation [into] the missing inquiry of two children in Brighton Beach area". ALSO READ: Body of missing girl, 10, found next to Cape Town dam "The suspects will be charged with kidnapping and murder. They will appear in court soon," Mbhele said. According to reports, one of the women was known to the boys. "The investigation is continuing, as police's Search and Rescue Team, K9 Unit members, Brighton Beach and Montclair police are still searching for the second child," she said.  KEEP UPDATED on the latest news by subscribing to our FREE newsletter. - FOLLOW News24 on Twitter   24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.  